articles.title: Many people over 60 still take aspirin for their heart, despite warnings - The Washington Post

articles.content: Nearly 30 percent (29.7) of those over age 60 still take a daily low dose of aspirin, despite guidelines advising against the drugs use as a primary way of preventing cardiovascular disease, a recent… [+191 chars]
